  "title": "Chinese Language Teacher (N2-P6) #82054",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Language School</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Chinese Language Teacher (N2-P6)</strong></li><li>Working Location: Upper Serangoon</li><li>Working Hours: 5-days rotating shifts (Mon-Sun: 10am-9pm) (5.5-days during probation)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic up to $2,800 - $3,600</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for teaching pre-school and primary level students</li><li>Teach using planned interactive activities such as drama and games for students from playgroup, pre-school, and primary levels</li><li>Update and communicate with parents after each class</li><li>Assess students and keep accurate records of their progress</li><li>Speak Mandarin clearly and accurately to handle questions, concerns, and feedback</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Candidates must have at least a Bachelor’s Degree in Education, Chinese Studies, Chinese Language, or other related fields</li><li>Good understanding of Singapore MOE Chinese Language curriculum</li><li>Passionate about learning and teaching</li><li>Familiar with Microsoft Office (e.g., Word, PowerPoint)</li><li>Able to work on Saturdays and/or Sundays (excluding Public Holidays)</li><li>At least 1 year of experience teaching Chinese</li><li>Plan, review, and evaluate lessons</li><li>Salary will be based on teaching experience</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#82054 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
